WEBVTT

00:06.249 --> 00:07.375
JACK HOSKINS: While I have you,
I was wondering

00:07.458 --> 00:08.999
if maybe you'd give me
a little sneak preview

00:09.083 --> 00:11.083
of what you're gonna be
talking about later.

00:11.333 --> 00:12.583
Well, I can tell you one thing.

00:12.667 --> 00:14.625
I'm afraid nobody's
going to believe me.

00:14.958 --> 00:16.917
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:17.416 --> 00:20.667
I believe that Terry Maitland,
Heath Hofstadter,

00:20.750 --> 00:21.583
Maria Canales...

00:21.667 --> 00:23.416
All three were not only
innocent,

00:23.875 --> 00:25.917
but I believe they were victims
themselves.

00:26.375 --> 00:30.416
The real killer was a malevolent
entity called El Cuco.

00:31.500 --> 00:33.917
This is what you've been doing
this whole time?!

00:34.166 --> 00:36.875
Going after the boogeyman?!
Are you insane?!

00:36.958 --> 00:40.166
All she's asking for
is we keep an open mind.

00:40.958 --> 00:43.708
I'm just gonna look for facts,
evidence...

00:43.792 --> 00:45.541
Dumb cop shit like that.

00:45.625 --> 00:47.541
HOLLY GIBNEY:
It kills every 27 days.

00:47.625 --> 00:48.625
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

00:48.958 --> 00:51.667
What I couldn't figure out
was... He was transforming.

00:51.750 --> 00:53.249
HOSKINS: At first,
I didn't understand

00:53.333 --> 00:54.625
what I was looking at.

00:55.792 --> 00:56.750
Stop!

00:57.500 --> 00:58.541
HOSKINS: But now I do.

00:58.958 --> 01:01.083
Best we just get to where
we're going.

01:03.500 --> 01:04.917
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:17.166 --> 01:24.208
♪ (OMINOUS DRONE) ♪

01:27.291 --> 01:29.999
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

01:37.917 --> 01:38.999
(INHALES SHARPLY)

01:45.792 --> 01:50.291
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:00.291 --> 02:05.541
♪ (TENSE STRING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:09.249 --> 02:10.833
(SIGHS)

02:47.541 --> 02:48.750
(SIGHS)

03:08.750 --> 03:10.458
We're down a chair.

03:10.541 --> 03:12.416
I don't want it in the house.

03:12.500 --> 03:14.208
So where is it?

03:14.291 --> 03:15.708
JEANNIE ANDERSON:
It's out back.

03:16.917 --> 03:19.667
Till the next garbage pickup.

03:19.750 --> 03:22.458
Unless you wanna take it
to the dump for me today.

03:24.083 --> 03:28.333
Ah, so we'll just invite our
single friends for dinner, then.

03:28.416 --> 03:30.917
I already ordered
a replacement online.

03:30.999 --> 03:32.999
They say we'll have it
by the end of the week.

03:34.999 --> 03:37.416
-It's done, then.
-JEANNIE: It is.

03:40.833 --> 03:42.083
And she's still sleeping?

03:42.166 --> 03:43.458
No, I don't believe so.

03:43.541 --> 03:46.458
I heard movement earlier,
and the front door.

03:47.792 --> 03:48.999
JEANNIE: So, she's not here?

03:49.792 --> 03:50.958
My guess is not.

03:52.249 --> 03:54.375
I don't get it.
Why so up-and-at-'em

03:54.458 --> 03:58.458
so early in the day in a town
she doesn't know anyone?

03:59.208 --> 04:01.583
How's she gonna get around?

04:01.667 --> 04:05.124
And where could she possibly go?
Did you talk to her?

04:06.041 --> 04:07.124
I was in bed.

04:08.124 --> 04:09.416
JEANNIE: Well, I wish you had.

04:10.291 --> 04:11.667
She's a big girl.

04:11.750 --> 04:14.291
I know that, Ralph.
I'm just saying.

04:17.999 --> 04:19.041
I gotta go.

04:29.333 --> 04:31.291
(SNIFFS, CLEARS THROAT)

04:47.750 --> 04:49.583
-(PHONE RINGING)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

04:49.667 --> 04:51.124
(SIGHS)

04:58.500 --> 04:59.875
(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

05:01.124 --> 05:03.667
Hey, does anybody out there
feel like working?

05:04.208 --> 05:05.583
God damn it!

05:06.249 --> 05:07.166
Who is this?

05:07.249 --> 05:08.750
GLORY MAITLAND:
Hi, Howie. It's Glory.

05:09.750 --> 05:11.416
Oh, hey, Glory.
Sorry about that.

05:11.500 --> 05:13.958
I think somebody
just stole my chew toy.

05:14.041 --> 05:15.249
How's it going, kid?

05:15.333 --> 05:18.166
-GLORY: Oh, you know.
-HOWIE: No, actually, I don't.

05:18.249 --> 05:20.124
GLORY: Well, I'm going back
to work today.

05:20.208 --> 05:22.999
-HOWIE: Good for you.
-GLORY: Yeah, the cupboards

05:23.083 --> 05:24.833
are getting a little light
on food.

05:24.917 --> 05:27.708
HOWIE: Hey, listen.
Have you given any more
thought to suing?

05:27.792 --> 05:30.708
(SIGHS) I just can't
put my mind to a lawsuit yet.

05:30.792 --> 05:33.708
HOWIE: No. You're right.
It's only been three weeks.

05:33.792 --> 05:35.166
No need to rush.

05:35.249 --> 05:36.917
Whenever you're ready, though.

05:36.999 --> 05:38.083
Thank you, Howie.

05:40.625 --> 05:41.750
(PHONE BEEPS)

05:44.333 --> 05:47.249
-Where are you going?
-GLORY: I'm going back to work!

05:47.333 --> 05:49.541
-Mom's gotta get out there.
-MAYA: Why?

05:49.625 --> 05:53.041
-JESSA: Stay with us.
-(LAUGHS) I would love to.

05:53.124 --> 05:55.625
But I will call you both
every chance I get, okay?

05:55.708 --> 05:57.667
Are people going to be
mean to you?

05:57.750 --> 06:00.208
GLORY: Why would they be?

06:00.291 --> 06:05.458
(SIGHS) Listen. There's a lot of
very nice people in this town,

06:05.541 --> 06:08.291
and I'm gonna go sell
a house to one of them.

06:09.124 --> 06:10.583
Good luck, Mom.

06:11.249 --> 06:13.458
Thank you. I love you.

06:14.583 --> 06:15.583
(KISSES)

06:16.667 --> 06:18.958
-Thank you, Dreena.
-It's my pleasure.

06:19.041 --> 06:20.958
GLORY: (KISSES) Bye, my sweets.

06:23.333 --> 06:25.667
-Back to work.
-Have a great day!

06:34.541 --> 06:36.083
(DOOR CREAKS)

07:22.041 --> 07:23.041
(SIGHS)

07:29.333 --> 07:30.541
How far is the barn?

07:33.541 --> 07:35.083
(TURNS ON RADIO)

07:35.166 --> 07:36.667
PREACHER: They laugh
in New York,

07:36.750 --> 07:40.792
and they laugh
in San Francisco, but they will
not be laughing

07:40.875 --> 07:43.792
when the mouth of Hell
opens up and sucks--

07:43.875 --> 07:47.500
♪ ("TRAVELLIN' MAN"
BY RICKY NELSON PLAYING) ♪

07:49.083 --> 07:52.750
HOLLY: Jack. How far is it
to the barn?

07:53.625 --> 07:57.124
♪ All over the world ♪

07:57.208 --> 08:00.208
You know, even when I was a kid,
I didn't believe in anything.

08:02.583 --> 08:05.833
Not God. Not the devil.

08:08.208 --> 08:09.208
Santa Claus.

08:11.124 --> 08:14.041
Superman. Boogeyman.

08:14.875 --> 08:15.917
None of it.

08:17.875 --> 08:19.416
But now, I believe.

08:22.917 --> 08:26.208
I very much fucking believe
there's something else out there

08:27.041 --> 08:29.249
that's worse
than I ever imagined.

08:31.958 --> 08:33.249
You're right to believe.

08:34.999 --> 08:36.041
So, what is it?

08:36.124 --> 08:40.208
♪ They're calling me, baby
Over the sea ♪

08:40.750 --> 08:44.750
Vampire? Satan?

08:47.291 --> 08:49.750
Joker? A guilty conscience?

08:50.833 --> 08:51.917
I don't know.

08:53.708 --> 08:54.750
JACK: How old is it?

08:56.416 --> 08:58.166
I don't know.

08:58.249 --> 09:04.667
My age? Centuries?
Before the Big Bang?

09:06.875 --> 09:11.124
Is there just the one,
or is there others?

09:14.083 --> 09:18.333
I don't know. I'm sorry.

09:19.833 --> 09:21.999
Then let me tell you
what I know.

09:22.083 --> 09:24.541
I know I'm just like that
poor bastard, Tracey,

09:24.625 --> 09:26.583
I heard you talking about
last night.

09:26.667 --> 09:28.833
Guy draws down a half-dozen
sharp shooters

09:28.917 --> 09:30.750
because all he wants is to die.

09:30.833 --> 09:31.917
(INHALES SHARPLY)

09:34.375 --> 09:35.500
So, question.

09:38.541 --> 09:40.416
Is that what's gonna
happen to me?

09:42.541 --> 09:47.375
Not if I can help it.
Not if I can track it, and...

09:48.333 --> 09:49.375
expose it.

09:51.083 --> 09:53.792
Which is why you're gonna
take me to the barn

09:53.875 --> 09:56.708
and show me what's in there
and let me go,

09:56.792 --> 09:59.500
so I can do what I have to to...
To stop it.

10:04.500 --> 10:06.208
You know I'm trying
to help you, right?

10:14.083 --> 10:16.041
-(CRUNCHING)
-(GROANS)

10:19.083 --> 10:20.124
(GROANS)

10:24.958 --> 10:27.083
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

10:37.875 --> 10:39.833
Take that road right up there.

10:39.917 --> 10:43.375
♪ When we walked
in the sands of Hawaii ♪

10:43.458 --> 10:46.792
♪ And I held you,
Oh, so tight ♪

10:46.875 --> 10:49.708
♪ (MUSIC GETS LOUDER) ♪

10:50.541 --> 10:53.083
(CELL BUZZING)

10:53.166 --> 10:55.792
♪ (DRAMATIC STRING MUSIC
PLAYING) ♪

10:55.875 --> 10:57.541
HOLLY: You've reached
Holly Gibney.

10:57.625 --> 10:59.416
-(RALPH SIGHS)
-HOLLY: I'm not here right now,
but please leave me your

10:59.500 --> 11:02.500
contact information and I will
get back to you as soon
as possible.

11:02.583 --> 11:03.999
-(BEEPING)
-Hey, Holly.

11:04.083 --> 11:07.375
It's, uh, Ralph Anderson again.
Can you call me back, please?

11:08.958 --> 11:10.583
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

11:14.083 --> 11:16.291
Oh, thanks, Yune.
I'll keep trying around.

11:16.375 --> 11:18.917
JACK: This is Jack Hoskins.
Not here right now.

11:18.999 --> 11:20.333
-Leave me a message.
-(BEEPING)

11:20.416 --> 11:25.041
Jack, give me a buzz, will you?
It's Ralph. Um...

11:26.166 --> 11:29.416
I'm trying to track down
Holly Gibney,

11:29.500 --> 11:31.375
the woman you met last night?

11:32.583 --> 11:34.833
So, um...

11:34.917 --> 11:37.375
-Yeah, just call me back.
-(BEEPING)

11:38.500 --> 11:41.541
(RALPH EXHALES)

11:41.625 --> 11:44.917
No, Howie. If she checks in,
have her call me back.

11:46.792 --> 11:48.583
No. I'm trying him now.

11:49.875 --> 11:52.541
PELLEY: No, Ralph, I haven't
heard from Holly,

11:52.625 --> 11:55.124
but did you, uh...
Did you talk to Jack?

11:55.208 --> 11:56.958
No answer. Why?

11:57.041 --> 11:59.625
Well, she seemed to be chumming
up with him last night.

11:59.708 --> 12:00.917
I don't know
if you noticed that.

12:00.999 --> 12:03.416
-Yeah, I did.
-PELLEY: A couple points there,

12:03.500 --> 12:05.458
he was her only friend
in the room.

12:05.541 --> 12:07.958
-True.
-PELLEY: He's not answering
his phone.

12:08.833 --> 12:11.291
She's not answering hers.

12:11.375 --> 12:13.208
I-- I'll meet you at his place.
Okay?

12:13.291 --> 12:14.416
Yeah, I'm on my way.

12:14.500 --> 12:15.583
RALPH: Okay.

12:15.667 --> 12:16.750
(KEYS JINGLING)

12:17.583 --> 12:20.208
♪ (HIP HOP MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

12:20.291 --> 12:21.333
LENNY: Hey, Claude.

12:24.708 --> 12:27.208
I gave you a little
farewell bonus.

12:27.291 --> 12:29.458
-You didn't have to do that.
-LENNY: Hey.

12:29.541 --> 12:31.333
Whenever my mom dumped me
in an orphanage

12:31.416 --> 12:32.750
to go off with the next
shit boyfriend,

12:32.833 --> 12:35.833
she always gave me a little
severance envelope, too, so...

12:35.917 --> 12:37.999
I guess that's just how
I was raised.

12:38.958 --> 12:40.917
Well, at least you got cash.

12:40.999 --> 12:42.875
Whenever I opened mine up,
moths flew out.

12:42.958 --> 12:44.291
(LAUGHS)

12:44.375 --> 12:45.875
Hey, thanks for this.

12:48.833 --> 12:50.917
So, what are you gonna
do with yourself?

12:50.999 --> 12:55.083
I don't know, man.
I might go back to Harvard.

12:55.166 --> 12:58.083
Finish off my PhD
in atomic brain surgery.

12:58.166 --> 12:59.291
(LAUGHS)
Funny guy.

12:59.375 --> 13:01.792
CLAUDE: Just ain't been
feeling like myself, lately.

13:01.875 --> 13:04.041
LENNY: Yeah, this place'll
do that to you.

13:04.583 --> 13:05.667
All right, bro.

13:07.667 --> 13:08.708
Thanks again.

13:11.124 --> 13:12.500
-I'll see you around.
-Yeah.

13:14.166 --> 13:17.208
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

13:27.208 --> 13:29.541
-JACK: Why me?
-What?

13:31.041 --> 13:32.708
Why did it pick me?

13:34.875 --> 13:36.875
This... thing...

13:39.458 --> 13:41.166
It's drawn to pain.

13:42.833 --> 13:44.249
JACK: Mm.

13:44.333 --> 13:47.041
HOLLY: Pain is... its wine.

13:50.708 --> 13:51.708
That's why you.

13:56.208 --> 13:58.750
You've been wronged
all your life.

13:59.667 --> 14:01.958
I don't know by who,
or by how many.

14:04.583 --> 14:06.249
My mother, for starters.

14:15.500 --> 14:18.583
How many shrinks does it take
to change a lightbulb?

14:24.416 --> 14:25.416
One.

14:26.708 --> 14:29.583
But the lightbulb
really has to wanna change.

14:36.249 --> 14:37.291
(CHUCKLES)

14:43.291 --> 14:45.166
GLORY: Let me show you
the master.

14:45.917 --> 14:47.792
This room is south facing,

14:47.875 --> 14:50.458
and there's a great view
out that window.

14:51.124 --> 14:52.124
Oh, wow.

14:53.458 --> 14:54.500
Very nice.

15:00.249 --> 15:01.291
GLORY: Excuse me.

15:03.166 --> 15:04.500
The kitchen is this way.

15:05.625 --> 15:08.792
All these appliances
come with the home.

15:08.875 --> 15:11.833
Oh, and I love this.
So convenient if you wanna

15:11.917 --> 15:14.416
fill a big pot for pasta, say.

15:15.958 --> 15:21.041
All these floors are original
hardwood, same in the bathrooms.

15:22.166 --> 15:24.083
How are the schools?

15:24.166 --> 15:25.875
Some of the best in the county.

15:28.625 --> 15:30.166
Good athletic program?

15:31.708 --> 15:32.708
Sure.

15:35.249 --> 15:36.541
Yep, it's me.

15:38.667 --> 15:39.999
Uh... Sorry?

15:40.083 --> 15:44.249
Mrs. Terry Maitland,
bride of Frankenstein?

15:44.333 --> 15:47.583
I'm here pitching my heart out,
and all you two can think about

15:47.667 --> 15:50.708
is which of your friends you're
gonna blab to about me first.

15:50.792 --> 15:52.750
-That's not fair.
-Okay, I'll tell you what.

15:52.833 --> 15:54.750
If you agree to go to contract
on this dump,

15:54.833 --> 15:56.541
you can take your camera out
right now,

15:56.625 --> 15:59.166
and I will rotate my head
360 degrees

15:59.249 --> 16:00.458
while spitting up guacamole.

16:00.541 --> 16:02.208
That's enough.

16:02.291 --> 16:04.375
Wait till you get a gander
at the guest room.

16:06.999 --> 16:10.541
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:11.375 --> 16:12.375
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

16:17.416 --> 16:18.875
PELLEY: Are we picking this?

16:21.708 --> 16:23.249
(LOCK RATTLING)

16:48.750 --> 16:50.625
RALPH: Ah, hey, Yune. Yeah.

16:51.958 --> 16:52.999
Uh, it's not good.

16:53.083 --> 16:56.750
Um... We should put
a BOLO out on her car and...

16:56.833 --> 17:00.083
I don't know what's happened,
but if they are together,

17:00.166 --> 17:04.750
then, um... we should consider
him armed and dangerous.

17:06.750 --> 17:07.750
Yeah.

17:09.458 --> 17:12.291
Shit, I hope that's his blood
and not hers.

17:12.917 --> 17:13.917
PELLEY: Yeah.

17:16.124 --> 17:19.416
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:44.958 --> 17:47.375
-HOWIE: Hey, Alec.
-PELLEY: Holly's missing.

17:47.458 --> 17:48.333
HOWIE: She what?

17:48.416 --> 17:50.249
PELLEY: We think she's
with Hoskins.

17:50.333 --> 17:52.291
HOWIE: Well, how do you know
they're together?

17:52.375 --> 17:53.708
Well, it's
a reasonable suspicion

17:53.792 --> 17:55.208
given what we know so far.

17:55.291 --> 17:56.792
Can you help us?

17:56.875 --> 17:59.958
Look, I am up to my ass
in appointments today.

18:00.041 --> 18:01.917
Let me call you back when
I catch a break, all right?

18:01.999 --> 18:04.750
You know what, Howard,
you got her into this.

18:04.833 --> 18:06.958
HOWIE: You're worried
about Jack Hoskins?

18:07.041 --> 18:08.583
Last night,
he was looking at her

18:08.667 --> 18:10.541
like she was the answer
to his prayers.

18:10.625 --> 18:12.917
Maybe they're off
on some playdate together.

18:12.999 --> 18:14.333
Oh, they're on a playdate?

18:14.416 --> 18:17.041
You know, why don't you come
over here and see the blood

18:17.124 --> 18:18.375
all over everything
for yourself,

18:18.458 --> 18:19.999
then we can talk
about a playdate.

18:20.083 --> 18:21.999
-HOWIE: I'll call you back
as soon as--
-(BEEPING)

18:22.750 --> 18:23.792
Alec?

18:35.166 --> 18:36.958
(CELL RINGING)

18:42.958 --> 18:43.999
(BEEPING)

18:45.333 --> 18:47.208
(CELL BUZZING)

18:54.667 --> 18:56.500
What has he forced you
to do for him?

18:57.583 --> 18:58.667
Oh, not much.

19:00.375 --> 19:04.875
A little food catering.
A little shopping.

19:04.958 --> 19:07.083
A little... spying.

19:11.750 --> 19:14.625
Why didn't you just stop me from
going to that meeting yesterday?

19:14.708 --> 19:17.249
Why didn't you just stop me from
telling everyone what I knew?

19:18.667 --> 19:20.333
Yet...

19:20.416 --> 19:22.541
you took me straight there,
and you...

19:23.458 --> 19:24.875
hung on every word.

19:26.708 --> 19:28.249
Even fought for me.

19:33.208 --> 19:35.083
Look how he's making you pay.

19:39.667 --> 19:41.583
Keep your eyes
on the road, please.

19:44.917 --> 19:48.667
I was really hoping you could
tell me so much more

19:48.750 --> 19:50.083
than you really can.

19:58.500 --> 20:00.291
(DOORBELL RINGS)

20:03.625 --> 20:04.875
-Hey, Ralph.
-Hey.

20:04.958 --> 20:05.917
(JEROME FUSSING)

20:05.999 --> 20:08.792
-How's Jerome?
-He's good.

20:08.875 --> 20:10.750
-RALPH: How are you?
-Good!

20:13.625 --> 20:16.291
Um, sorry, hold on for a second.

20:17.458 --> 20:19.792
(JEROME CRYING)

20:25.041 --> 20:27.750
TAMIKA: Wow, it's really
nice out today, huh?

20:29.750 --> 20:32.291
-What's up?
-RALPH: Um...

20:33.249 --> 20:36.041
I just wanna talk to you
about Jack.

20:36.124 --> 20:37.333
What'd he do now?

20:38.958 --> 20:41.500
We think he's, um...

20:41.583 --> 20:45.291
taken our investigator,
Holly Gibney.

20:46.500 --> 20:48.208
TAMIKA:
What do you mean, "taken"?

20:48.291 --> 20:51.958
Not exactly sure, but you guys
are pretty tight, right?

20:52.041 --> 20:54.625
You notice anything about him
in the last couple of days?

20:56.083 --> 20:58.416
I haven't seen him
since the christening.

20:58.500 --> 20:59.999
You were there, same as me.

21:01.583 --> 21:04.541
Yeah, you-- You remember
when you followed him outside?

21:04.625 --> 21:06.708
TAMIKA: Then why wouldn't you
hold my son?

21:09.291 --> 21:12.583
Yeah. I was asking him why
he was leaving so early.

21:12.667 --> 21:14.625
What did he have to say
to that?

21:15.667 --> 21:18.208
Just regular Jack bullshit.

21:18.291 --> 21:20.667
RALPH: Is there something
you're forgetting to tell me?

21:24.875 --> 21:27.249
Are you asking me
if I'm holding out on you?

21:27.333 --> 21:28.583
What the fuck, Ralph?

21:28.667 --> 21:30.583
(CHUCKLES)

21:30.667 --> 21:33.124
No, I'm asking you
if anyone's threatened you.

21:33.208 --> 21:34.375
Who, Jack?

21:40.083 --> 21:41.083
Okay, T.

21:42.208 --> 21:44.041
Send my love
to your family, yeah?

21:48.999 --> 21:50.041
Hey, Ralph.

21:53.708 --> 21:55.792
I was thinking when I come back
from maternity leave,

21:55.875 --> 21:57.792
I'm gonna transfer
to computer crimes.

21:57.875 --> 21:58.875
No!

22:02.083 --> 22:03.083
Why?

22:03.917 --> 22:05.375
I dunno. The baby.

22:07.500 --> 22:10.166
I don't think I can handle
the horror show anymore.

22:10.667 --> 22:12.583
Uh...

22:12.667 --> 22:16.041
I mean, it's not like I won't
be police anymore, just...

22:20.375 --> 22:21.583
I hope you find Jack.

22:24.541 --> 22:26.958
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

22:29.083 --> 22:31.958
LENNY: Jack hasn't been buying
the last few days,

22:32.041 --> 22:33.875
not that I'm complaining.

22:33.958 --> 22:36.625
Well, when he was last here,
did he seem to be...

22:37.083 --> 22:38.041
any kind of off?

22:38.124 --> 22:40.667
(CHUCKLES) Off?
Guy's a walking hand grenade

22:40.750 --> 22:41.999
with the pin half out.

22:42.083 --> 22:44.833
If he wasn't one of yours, I'd
have barred his ass years ago.

22:44.917 --> 22:46.333
Hey, is Claude working today?

22:46.416 --> 22:48.166
Um, Claude quit.

22:48.249 --> 22:50.750
-Did he say what his plans were?
-(CELL RINGING)

22:50.833 --> 22:54.208
Something about going back
to school, I think.

22:54.291 --> 22:59.541
Listen, if you do talk to Jack,
you should give us a ring, okay?

22:59.625 --> 23:01.124
Mm-hmm. Sure.

23:01.208 --> 23:02.833
That was Yune.

23:02.917 --> 23:04.416
He's pinged Holly's phone
for us.

23:04.500 --> 23:05.750
-Did he find it?
-Yeah.

23:05.833 --> 23:07.750
And guess whose phone's
in the same spot.

23:08.208 --> 23:09.249
Jack's.

23:09.958 --> 23:11.375
(TIRES SCREECH)

23:11.458 --> 23:13.541
RALPH: They're headed south
on old 22.

23:13.625 --> 23:15.999
They just passed Bartlow
and Pope township,

23:16.083 --> 23:17.041
two no-light towns.

23:17.124 --> 23:18.333
Are they gonna pull them over?

23:18.416 --> 23:20.333
Nah, I figure we can catch
up to them.

23:20.416 --> 23:21.500
I don't want them spooked.

23:21.583 --> 23:23.917
Oh, shit. Let's do it.

23:38.166 --> 23:40.416
(TURN SIGNAL CLICKS)

23:40.500 --> 23:42.708
-What are you doing?
-HOLLY: I have to go
to the bathroom.

23:42.792 --> 23:44.541
-JACK: Just hold it for a bit.
-HOLLY: I can't.

23:44.625 --> 23:46.625
-We're almost there.
-I have to go now.

24:09.875 --> 24:11.124
You need your bag to pee?

24:11.208 --> 24:13.083
I have to attend
to something else in there.

24:13.166 --> 24:14.333
Like what?

24:19.083 --> 24:23.416
Tell me, or you can just
go all over yourself right here.

24:23.500 --> 24:25.041
Please don't make me
spell it out.

24:25.124 --> 24:28.708
-I'll cover my ears. What?
-I have my period.

24:30.625 --> 24:31.667
Oh.

24:32.375 --> 24:34.333
Can I borrow your phone?

24:34.416 --> 24:37.541
-Why?
-Mine's about to die.

24:45.041 --> 24:48.708
♪ (TENSE STRING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

25:02.166 --> 25:04.416
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

25:19.249 --> 25:20.249
(GRUNTS)

26:42.958 --> 26:45.416
Holly! I have the keys!

26:45.500 --> 26:47.124
(CAR STARTS)

26:52.708 --> 26:53.999
-(GUNSHOT)
-(GRUNTS)

26:54.583 --> 26:56.500
(GUNFIRE)

26:58.917 --> 27:01.208
-(CAR HORN BLARING)
-Fuck!

27:06.833 --> 27:08.166
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

27:09.792 --> 27:10.833
(GRUNTS)

27:13.208 --> 27:15.500
(PANTING)

27:21.124 --> 27:23.833
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

27:44.375 --> 27:45.375
(GRUNTS)

27:54.208 --> 27:57.124
(PANTING)

27:59.249 --> 28:01.958
PELLEY: You've known Hoskins
a while, right?

28:02.041 --> 28:04.333
Does any of this line up?

28:04.416 --> 28:06.541
Look, I'm not a fan of the guy.

28:06.625 --> 28:09.333
Yeah, but this, I mean...

28:09.416 --> 28:11.291
We're operating under
the assumption

28:11.375 --> 28:12.750
that he kidnapped somebody.

28:14.291 --> 28:15.291
We are.

28:16.500 --> 28:17.541
So, why?

28:21.750 --> 28:24.083
You know, since the moment
that I arrived

28:24.166 --> 28:25.958
at the Frankie Peterson
murder site,

28:26.041 --> 28:27.541
nothing's made sense.

28:27.625 --> 28:29.875
Nothing in my life.
You know, I can't...

28:33.667 --> 28:36.124
I really can't connect
the dots on any of it.

28:38.416 --> 28:39.458
(SIGHS)

28:40.750 --> 28:42.958
You know, one summer,
when I was a kid...

28:44.416 --> 28:46.500
we spent a couple weeks
at a lake.

28:47.583 --> 28:49.792
And I got lost in the woods.

28:49.875 --> 28:52.708
You know, one second,
I'm screwing around with

28:52.792 --> 28:54.708
my brother and some other kids,

28:54.792 --> 28:57.416
the next thing I know,
I'm all alone,

28:57.500 --> 28:59.291
no idea how to get back.

28:59.375 --> 29:03.166
And then it gets dark,
then it gets cold.

29:03.249 --> 29:06.041
And they find me
at 4:00 in the morning,

29:06.124 --> 29:09.041
these two hunters, right?
Part of a search party.

29:09.124 --> 29:12.667
My parents, and cops,
and the rangers.

29:14.708 --> 29:16.124
Now, here's the thing.

29:17.833 --> 29:19.041
Before they found me...

29:21.541 --> 29:27.166
I heard something call my name.
And I heard it twice.

29:28.708 --> 29:29.999
You imagined it.

29:31.833 --> 29:34.667
Yeah, see, that's what everybody
said back then, too.

29:35.833 --> 29:38.083
But that's not what happened.

29:38.166 --> 29:40.999
No, I was a tough little kid
back then, I was.

29:42.958 --> 29:44.458
I was tough as hell.

29:45.999 --> 29:49.708
But hearing whatever that was
say my name...

29:51.708 --> 29:54.500
To this day, I've never been
so shit scared.

29:58.958 --> 29:59.999
Huh.

30:04.875 --> 30:07.083
Yeah. "Huh."

30:30.917 --> 30:33.792
So, they may file charges.

30:33.875 --> 30:37.041
-For what, exactly?
-Emotional distress.

30:40.917 --> 30:43.875
I never should've let you come
back to work. It was too early.

30:45.583 --> 30:47.625
Like there will ever be
a right time?

30:49.249 --> 30:50.249
Probably not.

30:52.041 --> 30:54.541
I could make calls to other
agencies, but I don't imagine

30:54.625 --> 30:57.124
it's gonna be any different
anywhere else.

30:57.208 --> 30:59.291
Well, I need to make a living.

30:59.375 --> 31:00.917
We're closing in on broke!

31:02.583 --> 31:05.583
Well, if it was me,
I'd sell my house.

31:07.583 --> 31:09.583
-And move to where?
-LORRAINE: Anywhere.

31:09.667 --> 31:11.625
You and the girls need
a fresh start.

31:13.667 --> 31:15.541
No.

31:15.625 --> 31:17.583
Terry and I raised our family
in that house.

31:17.667 --> 31:19.458
I'm not putting the girls
through that.

31:20.083 --> 31:21.375
We're staying put.

31:21.458 --> 31:22.458
LORRAINE: All right.

31:22.541 --> 31:24.416
Well, if you change your mind,

31:24.500 --> 31:27.083
I promise I'll get you
the highest price possible.

31:29.208 --> 31:30.249
Thank you.

31:32.625 --> 31:35.625
You know what? You're right.

31:35.708 --> 31:38.458
I wouldn't let them run me
out of town either.

31:38.541 --> 31:40.999
Not after everything
they've put you through.

31:46.375 --> 31:52.458
♪ (EERIE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

32:02.249 --> 32:03.708
(DIALING ON PHONE)

32:09.999 --> 32:12.667
-HOWIE: Hey, Glory.
-Let's sue.

32:12.750 --> 32:16.541
-Who do you wanna sue?
-GLORY: The P.D., for starters.

32:16.625 --> 32:18.999
That goes without saying.
Who else?

32:19.667 --> 32:21.291
GLORY: You tell me.

32:21.375 --> 32:23.375
District Attorney's office.

32:23.458 --> 32:25.124
Country Department
of Corrections.

32:25.208 --> 32:27.083
They were responsible
for Terry's safety

32:27.166 --> 32:28.249
when he went to court.

32:28.333 --> 32:29.917
GLORY: And what about
the court grounds?

32:29.999 --> 32:31.833
That would be
the County Court's office.

32:31.917 --> 32:33.208
Make them pay, too.

32:33.291 --> 32:35.875
How about any of their
individual players?

32:35.958 --> 32:36.958
You wanna go after them?

32:37.041 --> 32:38.333
Let me think about that.

32:38.416 --> 32:41.458
Listen, once we go ahead with
this, you should be prepared--

32:41.541 --> 32:42.833
(BEEPING)

32:50.375 --> 32:54.667
So, the clerk was on his
smartphone the whole time.

32:54.750 --> 32:56.999
Earbuds in.
Saw nothing, heard nothing.

32:57.083 --> 32:58.500
What have you got? Anything?

32:58.583 --> 33:00.708
Well, it's clear where
the car peeled out.

33:01.249 --> 33:02.249
Right.

33:03.708 --> 33:09.333
Okay, well, a car pulled out.
We-- We can't be sure... whose.

33:09.416 --> 33:11.291
We got this over here.

33:11.375 --> 33:14.750
RALPH: Yeah, right. Sablo said
that the cell tower ping

33:14.833 --> 33:17.750
stopped around here,
and then they cut out. Okay.

33:18.999 --> 33:20.999
And it's hers. God damn him.

33:23.041 --> 33:24.083
Is she dead?

33:27.416 --> 33:29.291
How the fuck am I supposed
to answer that?

33:29.375 --> 33:30.458
Well, what's your gut saying?

33:30.541 --> 33:32.375
My gut says,
"I don't fucking know."

33:32.458 --> 33:36.083
We can drive around here,
we can look for the car.

33:36.166 --> 33:39.124
But he's got 90 minutes'
head start on us.

33:39.208 --> 33:40.500
-RALPH: So...
-(SIRENS BLARING)

33:40.583 --> 33:43.416
Uh, we're about to be relieved
of our duties here anyway.

33:45.041 --> 33:48.083
-We should fill them in.
-No, Sablo's already done it.

33:48.166 --> 33:50.249
Let's just make sure they
don't miss this,

33:50.333 --> 33:51.583
and then we can go.

33:53.625 --> 33:55.792
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

33:59.875 --> 34:00.917
(INHALES SHARPLY)

34:18.958 --> 34:20.124
(GASPING)

34:22.333 --> 34:25.500
(GAGS)

34:32.124 --> 34:34.792
(SPLUTTERS)

34:41.958 --> 34:42.958
Fuck!

34:45.208 --> 34:46.291
Fuck!

34:49.124 --> 34:50.500
(GRUNTS)

35:02.667 --> 35:03.667
(GUNSHOT)

35:14.583 --> 35:15.667
HOWIE: Hello?

35:20.208 --> 35:21.291
Door was unlocked.

35:26.249 --> 35:28.166
At first, I thought he was
an ally,

35:28.249 --> 35:30.625
and so,
I thought nothing of him,

35:30.708 --> 35:33.708
and he wanted to show me
something in the barn,

35:34.541 --> 35:35.792
like he said.

35:35.875 --> 35:38.750
Uh, then I saw
the wound on his neck.

35:38.833 --> 35:41.333
My next thought was that
he was delivering me up

35:41.416 --> 35:44.333
like Tracey Powell delivered
those sisters in Dayton.

35:45.708 --> 35:47.041
But then, no.

35:47.833 --> 35:50.208
I think it only
feeds on children.

35:54.375 --> 35:56.249
On the other hand,
if it's hungry enough,

35:56.333 --> 35:57.583
or desperate enough...

35:59.625 --> 36:01.166
Finally, I came
to the conclusion

36:01.249 --> 36:03.333
that he was taking me somewhere
to, um...

36:03.875 --> 36:04.875
eliminate me.

36:07.875 --> 36:11.041
He was really, really struggling
with that, Jack.

36:12.375 --> 36:14.249
But he had no choice
in the matter.

36:15.249 --> 36:16.500
"Devil made me do it."

36:16.583 --> 36:19.041
A devil made him do it. Yes.

36:19.124 --> 36:22.667
Mark on his neck, on Tracey.
It's how he controls them.

36:22.750 --> 36:26.083
He gets into their minds,
into their pain centers,

36:26.166 --> 36:28.667
their memories, their souls.

36:28.750 --> 36:33.291
It nestles in their heads
and looks through their eyes.

36:34.291 --> 36:36.917
And those poor people, it...

36:38.083 --> 36:39.124
Once it's in...

36:41.208 --> 36:43.792
the only way they'll ever
experience freedom

36:43.875 --> 36:45.833
is through death.

36:45.917 --> 36:50.375
Did Jack give you any idea
where he was headed?

36:53.124 --> 36:55.124
He's wherever this thing
wants him to be.

36:56.625 --> 36:59.249
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:09.249 --> 37:10.291
JACK: Hey!

37:13.458 --> 37:14.458
Hey!

37:48.041 --> 37:50.625
SABLO: One last thing.
You ever seen this man before?

37:57.416 --> 37:59.166
No. But...

38:01.708 --> 38:02.708
But?

38:03.333 --> 38:04.667
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

38:05.083 --> 38:06.124
No.

38:10.541 --> 38:12.833
Well, why don't you
hold on to that?

38:12.917 --> 38:15.500
In case something occurs to you.

38:19.500 --> 38:21.500
ANDY: I'm looking for
Holly Gibney.

38:30.208 --> 38:32.792
Yeah. I shoulda called first.

38:32.875 --> 38:34.208
Uh, what are you doing here?

38:38.999 --> 38:43.208
Damn it, you had me going there
for a minute! (LAUGHS)

38:49.208 --> 38:51.208
-SABLO: She tells some story.
-RALPH: Yeah, she does.

38:52.875 --> 38:54.291
They got an all-points on him.

38:54.375 --> 38:56.708
Cops are staking out
his apartment and his car.

38:56.792 --> 38:57.917
-Yeah.
-Nothing so far.

38:57.999 --> 38:58.999
Right.

38:59.083 --> 39:02.333
The thing about that barn
that he was supposedly

39:02.416 --> 39:03.999
taking her to...

39:04.083 --> 39:05.875
The gas station where he was
letting shots go,

39:05.958 --> 39:08.500
that's two hours
in the opposite direction.

39:08.583 --> 39:11.708
-What about his cell?
-It's turned off.

39:11.792 --> 39:13.416
Here's the thing that
I don't understand, right?

39:13.500 --> 39:17.291
When all's said and done,
why would he even wanna...

39:18.041 --> 39:20.333
kill her in the first place?

39:20.416 --> 39:25.708
I think maybe she told you why.
You just didn't wanna hear it.

39:27.249 --> 39:28.999
She doesn't strike me as crazy.

39:29.083 --> 39:31.083
She's weird, okay,
but she's not crazy.

39:31.166 --> 39:32.999
Somebody wanted her
off the board today.

39:33.083 --> 39:36.416
She barely had time to unpack,
and someone wanted her gone.

39:37.667 --> 39:40.333
I showed her
Claude Bolton's mugshot.

39:40.416 --> 39:42.375
I just asked her if she
knew who he was.

39:42.458 --> 39:44.625
Well, what--
What was her answer?

39:46.291 --> 39:50.375
She'd never seen him before.
But I could tell it rang a bell.

39:50.458 --> 39:51.667
Not like she was
hiding something,

39:51.750 --> 39:53.625
but more like she couldn't
put her finger on it.

39:54.291 --> 39:56.041
Well, thank you.

39:56.124 --> 39:58.583
Thanks for that, you gassing
her head up even more

39:58.667 --> 40:01.500
than it already was. No, really,
I appreciate that.

40:03.333 --> 40:06.333
Here's the difference
between you and me.

40:06.416 --> 40:08.708
You need this whole thing
to make some kind of sense

40:08.792 --> 40:10.166
that you can live with.

40:10.917 --> 40:12.333
I just want it to end.

40:15.458 --> 40:16.958
Be in touch if we find him.

40:51.208 --> 40:52.917
ANDY: Ralph.

40:52.999 --> 40:55.750
I want you to understand that
I've been doing my own research

40:55.833 --> 40:58.083
on Heath Hofstadter
since I met Holly.

40:58.166 --> 40:59.917
Naturally, that led me
to Terry Maitland

40:59.999 --> 41:02.708
and everything else that you've
been looking at.

41:03.750 --> 41:05.124
Okay.

41:05.208 --> 41:08.667
Look, what I'm saying is,
what I'm hoping for is that...

41:08.750 --> 41:11.375
That I can be a part of this
thing with you and your crew.

41:12.208 --> 41:15.500
I'm a good detective. I was.

41:15.583 --> 41:17.333
Ah, what difference
does it make?

41:17.416 --> 41:20.041
But I have never been shy about
pushing up my sleeves,

41:20.124 --> 41:22.166
getting in the dirt
with the humps.

41:22.249 --> 41:23.667
-HOLLY: Hey!
-You--

41:28.041 --> 41:29.041
HOLLY: You knew.

41:30.667 --> 41:34.124
Oh, that there was a vague
resemblance between that sketch

41:34.208 --> 41:35.500
and Claude Bolton? Yeah, I knew.

41:35.583 --> 41:38.333
And is it true that the Terry
version of it scratched Claude?

41:40.500 --> 41:42.583
-Yeah, it is.
-HOLLY: When?

41:43.583 --> 41:45.375
Why didn't you tell me?

41:45.458 --> 41:48.083
After everything I told you
yesterday about Terry

41:48.166 --> 41:49.875
having been scratched
by Heath Hofstadter,

41:49.958 --> 41:51.750
who was probably scratched
by Maria Can--

41:51.833 --> 41:53.625
Caneles? Yes. Yes.

41:53.708 --> 41:56.041
So, why didn't you
say something?

41:57.083 --> 41:58.124
Nah.

41:59.208 --> 42:01.917
No, you don't get to do this
anymore, Ralph.

42:03.708 --> 42:04.708
Do what?

42:04.792 --> 42:07.249
Play like it's reasonable
and rational to ignore

42:07.333 --> 42:10.124
everything that's unreasonable
and irrational

42:10.208 --> 42:12.917
that's happening
right in front of your face.

42:12.999 --> 42:14.333
If you guys are gonna
stop this thing,

42:14.416 --> 42:16.792
you need to start getting
over yourself.

42:16.875 --> 42:19.416
If you can't, or you won't
allow that to happen,

42:19.500 --> 42:21.583
then you need to just
step to the side.

42:22.667 --> 42:23.999
Because right now,
you're standing

42:24.083 --> 42:25.500
in everyone else's way.

42:55.500 --> 42:56.500
He--

42:56.583 --> 42:58.375
I'm aware that this is
an imposition,

42:58.458 --> 43:00.375
and I apologize for calling
like this,

43:00.458 --> 43:02.917
but I wouldn't if it wasn't
an emergency.

43:05.375 --> 43:07.291
Thank you. I'll be there
in an hour.

43:08.166 --> 43:09.208
(BEEPING)

43:09.708 --> 43:10.708
(SIGHS)

43:17.750 --> 43:18.792
(SNIFFS)

43:58.667 --> 44:02.124
-What do you believe in?
-I'm sorry?

44:02.208 --> 44:04.375
RALPH: Um... God.
Do you believe in God?

44:06.208 --> 44:10.249
ZUCKER: You know my personal
beliefs aren't relevant, right?

44:10.333 --> 44:11.875
RALPH: Right, what about
Heaven and Hell?

44:11.958 --> 44:14.166
Do you believe that they exist?

44:15.375 --> 44:17.041
Fine. What about evil?

44:19.208 --> 44:21.041
Do you believe in the concept
of evil?

44:23.625 --> 44:26.750
ZUCKER: Whenever I hear evil,
I think "medieval".

44:26.833 --> 44:27.875
Okay, but...

44:29.541 --> 44:31.166
do you believe in it?

44:31.249 --> 44:32.958
I believe in cause and effect,

44:33.041 --> 44:35.500
and I believe
in medical research.

44:35.583 --> 44:39.124
Okay, so, for you, um...

44:40.208 --> 44:44.416
any kind of, um,
negative behavior, uh,

44:44.500 --> 44:49.416
is due to either bad parenting,
bad genes,

44:49.500 --> 44:52.875
uh, bad brain chemistry, right?
There's no such thing, for you,

44:52.958 --> 44:56.917
as evil in the world without
some rational explanation.

44:58.291 --> 44:59.833
If I wanted to be
a voodoo doctor,

44:59.917 --> 45:01.792
I'd have gone
to voodoo med school.

45:03.124 --> 45:05.249
Tell me what's going on
with you.

45:05.333 --> 45:07.083
You said it was an emergency.

45:09.083 --> 45:11.875
Yeah. Oh, there's...

45:11.958 --> 45:14.541
There's just some stuff
that's happening now,

45:14.625 --> 45:16.792
that's unfolding now,
that is, um...

45:17.875 --> 45:18.958
That's just...

45:22.917 --> 45:25.291
It's-- It's too much for me.

45:27.792 --> 45:32.124
ZUCKER: Ralph,
you need to be specific.

45:38.291 --> 45:41.917
I know you're suffering.
